# Backend Go architecture conventions

- Keep business logic in `pkg/services/<domain>/`; keep API handlers thin.
- Follow existing service interfaces and package boundaries in the touched area.
- If dependency wiring changes, run `make gen-go` (Wire).
- If feature toggles change, run `make gen-feature-toggles`.
- If schema generation inputs change, run the matching generators (`make gen-cue`, `make swagger-gen`, etc.).
- Add or update focused Go tests for behavior changes.
- Prefer targeted test runs during iteration (`go test -run TestName ./path/...`).

